320.5	Marshall_McLuhan	Marshall McLuhan	Herbert Marshall McLuhan, CC (July 21, 1911 – December 31, 1980) was a Canadian educator, philosopher, and scholar—a professor of English literature, a literary critic, a rhetorician, and a communication theorist. McLuhan's work is viewed as one of the cornerstones of the study of media theory, as well as having practical applications in the advertising and television industries.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Marshall_McLuhan_holding_a_mirror.jpg/250px-Marshall_McLuhan_holding_a_mirror.jpg
